    "objective": "“to investigate the pharmacokinetics of PHY in critically ill children using a population PK (mixed-effects) modelling approach, with the specific focus on the disposition of the protein-unbound drug”",
    "covariates": "Tested: albumin, WT, LBW, AGE, serum creatinine, renal function Included: albumin on partition coefficient, WT on CL, V2, V3",
    "observations": "Contrary to earlier models, PHT PK was described not using michaelis menten kinetics, but instead using albumin as a covariate on clearance depending on unbound concentrations. Unbound concentrations were described, which may lead to a better understanding of the exposure-response of PHT",
    "dose": "Oral and IV doses in patients",
    "structure": "2 compartment model with first order absorption and elimination, and partition of bound and unbound PHT",
